The scientific foundations of integrated and systemic approach, the manifestation of a sustainable worldview in various areas of life are discussed, and co-creative group processes that promote sustainability are studied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main goal is the expansion of the perception of sustainability into all fields of human activity and connecting sustainable worldview with co-creational group processes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student - understands the basics of a sustainable worldview and can relate sustainability to very different areas of life; - understands the interconnectedness of processes on Earth, the role of cooperation and competition in both evolution and human society; - experiences co-creative group processes and acquires knowledge and skills to use these methods independently.
